142
00:16:05.790 --> 00:16:07.500
- What do we want?
- Pushers out!

143
00:16:07.584 --> 00:16:09.127
- When do we want them?
- Now!

144
00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:12.005
- Pusher, pusher, pusher!
- Out, out, out!

145
00:16:26.102 --> 00:16:29.647
Look who's got hisself a new girlfriend.

146
00:16:32.567 --> 00:16:37.405
- We'll see you there, then, John.
- Yeah, go on ahead.

147
00:16:37.488 --> 00:16:41.993
- What the hell do you want?
- Is that any way to talk to a lady?

148
00:16:42.076 --> 00:16:44.662
Ladies don't go calling
on gentleman unannounced.

149
00:16:44.746 --> 00:16:46.831
So we're a gentleman now, are we?

150
00:16:46.915 --> 00:16:50.418
Where's your manners?
You didn't introduce me to your friends.

151
00:16:50.501 --> 00:16:53.588
- If that's what you're after.
- You closing up early?

152
00:16:53.671 --> 00:16:56.341
One of the benefits of being self-employed.

153
00:16:56.424 --> 00:17:02.096
You're amazing, John.
No, really, you're a model of... profitability.

154
00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:06.309
How to succeed in business
without any customers.

155
00:17:06.392 --> 00:17:08.311
- I do well enough.
- Yeah, well...

156
00:17:08.394 --> 00:17:11.898
There must be a few bob
in those brothels there on Rathgar Road.

157
00:17:11.981 --> 00:17:14.651
What they worth now, John?

158
00:17:14.734 --> 00:17:19.447
- You're a dangerous little bitch.
- Ah, well. Do my best. Buy us a drink?

159
00:17:19.531 --> 00:17:25.203
