- You and Dad.

448
00:39:59.557 --> 00:40:01.643
Yeah.

449
00:40:03.269 --> 00:40:07.440
I am listening, actually. Whoever did it
made sure I was not in the room.

450
00:40:09.192 --> 00:40:11.903
Could you do this? You're better at it.

451
00:40:11.986 --> 00:40:15.073
- There's nothing to worry about.
- Nothing to worry about?

452
00:40:15.156 --> 00:40:19.702
I'm the only Guerin in the phone book.
Who do you think they'll come after next?

453
00:40:19.786 --> 00:40:23.081
Don't flatter yourself, little brother.

454
00:40:23.164 --> 00:40:26.209
Are you going to dance on this
or are you gonna go fast on it?

455
00:40:26.292 --> 00:40:30.255
- Here, give someone else a go.
- Give me a turn!

456
00:41:08.668 --> 00:41:11.087
Are you coming to bed?

457
00:41:12.046 --> 00:41:14.632
- What?
- I know you can hear me. Coming to bed?

458
00:41:14.716 --> 00:41:16.551
I'll be along in a minute.

459
00:41:18.469 --> 00:41:21.180
Fine. Suit yourself.

460
00:41:25.727 --> 00:41:29.480
Turn it down. Turn it down!

461
00:41:30.815 --> 00:41:35.320
Come on. I love it. I love my work.

462
00:41:35.403 --> 00:41:38.948
I'm finally doing something
that can make a difference.

463
00:41:39.032 --> 00:41:41.743
What am I gonna do with you?

464
00:41:42.535 --> 00:41:44.329
- Oh, come on.
- No.

465
00:41:56.382 --> 00:41:58.593
OK.

466
00:42:04.641 --> 00:42:06.726
Come on, man.

467
00:42:07.644 --> 00:42:10.688
Come on. Good boy!

468
00:42:17.737 --> 00:42:19.822
Did we wake you up?

469
00:42:25.662 --> 00:42:30.583
What can I say?
I don't think Gerry Hutch is into drugs.

470
00:42:30.667 --> 00:42:33.878
The Brinks heist, probably.
But drugs is just not his scene.

471
00:42:33.962 --> 00:42:37.215
I understand, but I've been
tracking his movements.

472
00:42:37.298 --> 00:42:41.135
I just need to source the drugs.
The connection's easy. I need your help.

473
00:42:41.219 --> 00:42:46.099
- I need you to stop coming to my office.
- He's got the money.

474
00:42:46.182 --> 00:42:49.811
We're talking about a fella
with no visible source of income

475
00:42:49.894 --> 00:42:52.605
who paid tax on £2 million last year.

476
00:42:52.689 --> 00:42:55.608
It's laundered
through the government's tax amnesty.

477
00:42:55.692 --> 00:42:59.904
- He's got too much money not to be into it.
- In your esteemed journalistic opinion.

478
00:42:59.988 --> 00:43:03.908
I know you seized shipments from Cork.
It's coming from somewhere. Where?

479
00:43:03.992 --> 00:43:08.037
We've impounded drugs from
Liverpool, Scotland, Amsterdam, Pakistan.

480
00:43:08.121 --> 00:43:12.750
You're not the only one trying here, and
Hutch isn't the only one with dirty money.

481
00:43:12.834 --> 00:43:15.837
- Who else you got?
- I could name you a dozen.

482
00:43:15.920 --> 00:43:19.090
Here's the latest candidate,
just in from Interpol.

483
00:43:19.173 --> 00:43:21.759
John Gilligan, one year
out of Portlaoise Prison.

484
00:43:21.843 --> 00:43:24.262
Can you tell me
how this Ballyfermot lowlife

485
00:43:24.345 --> 00:43:29.225
has £300,000 to launder in an Amsterdam
casino? You're the star journalist.

486
00:43:29.309 --> 00:43:31.519
Gilligan. Certainly keeps a low profile.

487
00:43:31.603 --> 00:43:32.770
Yeah?

488
00:43:32.854 --> 00:43:35.481
Hi, Aengus. Yeah, can you hold?

489
00:43:35.565 --> 00:43:37.442
- Can I... ?
- Go on. It's a copy.

490
00:43:37.525 --> 00:43:39.485
- Great.
- Just go.

491
00:43:39.569 --> 00:43:41.654
I owe you lunch.

492
00:43:43.323 --> 00:43:46.367
No, run the Brinks story.
Just hold off on the drugs claim.

493
00:43:46.451 --> 00:43:49.913
What for? This stuff you sent is great.

494
00:43:49.996 --> 00:43:53.333
Just give me 24 hours.
I got a tip. This could be big.

495
00:43:53.416 --> 00:43:58.421
- I'm trusting you on this one, Veronica.
- Oh, aren't you great!

496
00:44:09.224 --> 00:44:11.726
Nice tan there, John!

497
00:44:13.436 --> 00:44:15.813
Hope there's no hard feelings between us.

498
00:44:15.897 --> 00:44:21.611
I'm not one to take a bullet
through my window personally.

499
00:44:21.694 --> 00:44:24.113
Get lost.

500
00:44:24.197 --> 00:44:27.325
I told you to be careful
with the likes of Gerry Hutch.

501
00:44:27.408 --> 00:44:31.913
But you didn't tell me
about a fella named Gilligan.

502
00:44:31.996 --> 00:44:32.997
Who?

503
00:44:33.081 --> 00:44:35.917
You provided him with a car
when he got out of prison.

504
00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:38.628
John Gilligan. Do you want me to spell it?

505
00:44:38.711 --> 00:44:42.215
I run a bleedin' garage.
I provide loads of cars to people.

506
00:44:42.298 --> 00:44:45.176
Hardly gonna remember
every one of them, now, am I?

507
00:44:45.260 --> 00:44:49.931
- Is that him there?
- Why should I give a shite?

508
00:44:50.014 --> 00:44:55.144
No reason, really. Just the fella behind
the security guard looks a lot like you.

509
00:44:56.521 --> 00:45:00.108
- Now, there's a coincidence.
- Where's his money coming from?

510
00:45:00.191 --> 00:45:02.569
Is he providing
hash and heroin to Mitchell?

511
00:45:02.652 --> 00:45:06.197
I can't help you, Veronica.
Don't know nothing about him.

512
00:45:06.281 --> 00:45:09.200
If I hear of anything,
I'll let you know, OK? Molly!

513
00:45:09.284 --> 00:45:13.454
You can keep the photo if you like.
It's a nice one of you. We got plenty.

514
00:45:18.293 --> 00:45:21.337
- You sell horses yourself?
- I do.

515
00:45:21.421 --> 00:45:25.717
- You have a number.
- I sell them on to Germany mostly.

516
00:45:25.800 --> 00:45:29.596
Myself and Geraldine are planning
to make this the largest and finest

517
00:45:29.679 --> 00:45:33.600
equestrian centre in all of Ireland.

518
00:45:33.683 --> 00:45:37.020
Well, I must say the size is impressive.

519
00:45:37.103 --> 00:45:38.980
Said the nun to the sailor.

520
00:45:40.190 --> 00:45:46.112
How about an aperitif?
Some champers, caviar? It's all imported.

521
00:45:46.196 --> 00:45:49.490
John and I have great plans for this place.

522
00:45:49.574 --> 00:45:51.659
Hang on.

523
00:45:52.994 --> 00:45:55.079
Hello?

524
00:45:55.163 --> 00:45:56.456
- Hello?
- John...

525
00:45:56.539 --> 00:46:00.043
You're breaking up there. Hello?

526
00:46:00.126 --> 00:46:02.170
- It's Traynor.
- Johnny.

527
00:46:02.253 --> 00:46:06.591
Listen, Veronica Guerin's got hold of
a photo of us in Amsterdam.

528
00:46:06.674 --> 00:46:13.097
But, John, I swear I had nothing
to do with it. I never mentioned your name.

529
00:46:13.181 --> 00:46:15.266
But she was asking about you.

530
00:46:15.350 --> 00:46:21.564
Johnny, I told you before, if she so much
as mentions my fucking name, you pay.

531
00:46:24.734 --> 00:46:27.028
Fucking eejits!

532
00:46:27.111 --> 00:46:29.197
Fuck 'em!

533
00:46:34.494 --> 00:46:36.579
Happy Christmas!

534
00:46:39.290 --> 00:46:42.168
- Now, isn't this great?
- When's Mum coming here?

535
00:46:42.252 --> 00:46:46.047
She'll be here soon.
We'll want something stronger than that.

536
00:46:51.177 --> 00:46:53.638
Yeah? Ma, how are you?

537
00:46:53.721 --> 00:46:57.058
- Happy Christmas, Ann. You look great.
- Happy Christmas.

538
00:46:57.141 --> 00:47:01.020
- Where's your mum?
- You know her. Always going for the gold.

539
00:47:01.938 --> 00:47:03.857
All right.

540
00:47:05.066 --> 00:47:06.818
There's someone at the door, Ma.

541
00:47:06.901 --> 00:47:10.446
My phone'll be on all night.
You can call me whenever you want.

542
00:47:10.530 --> 00:47:13.658
I love you too. OK. Bye. Bye.

543
00:47:21.332 --> 00:47:23.710
Yeah, all right, all right.

544
00:48:31.903 --> 00:48:34.405
Veronica's been shot!

545
00:48:40.453 --> 00:48:41.496
How are you?

546
00:48:41.579 --> 00:48:43.873
- How are you?
- You look gorgeous.

547
00:48:43.957 --> 00:48:47.585
- Look at you. For God's sake.
- Hey, Willy.

548
00:48:49.045 --> 00:48:51.923
Can't find any sport on. Can you believe it?

549
00:48:52.006 --> 00:48:55.885
... extensive investigations
into organised crime in Dublin...

550
00:48:55.969 --> 00:48:59.556
Why do they always use
that brutal picture?

551
00:48:59.639 --> 00:49:01.474
It was a very serious incident.

552
00:49:01.558 --> 00:49:05.520
Veronica Guerin
is a very talented journalist.

553
00:49:05.603 --> 00:49:09.649
An attack like this could be seen
as an attempt to muzzle her

554
00:49:09.732 --> 00:49:14.696
because of certain publications
or articles she wrote.

555
00:49:14.779 --> 00:49:18.116
This would be connected
with last month's £3 million robbery?

556
00:49:18.199 --> 00:49:21.828
We all know who pulled that one,
don't we, Hutch? He threatened me.

557
00:49:21.911 --> 00:49:25.623
Veronica, please, stop this.
Write about fashion, about football.

558
00:49:25.707 --> 00:49:29.836
Write about anything you like, but stop this.
You don't have to do it any more.

559
00:49:29.919 --> 00:49:35.049
I don't see myself covering the catwalks
or doing a gardening column, Aengus.

560
00:49:35.133 --> 00:49:38.177
You've always wanted
to write about politics.

561
00:49:38.261 --> 00:49:40.555
I am. Drugs are political.

562
00:49:40.638 --> 00:49:43.600
What if I told you
I wouldn't publish your stuff any more?

563
00:49:43.683 --> 00:49:45.560
But you never would tell me that.

564
00:49:45.643 --> 00:49:48.479
For Christ's sake, there's no sport channel.

565
00:49:48.563 --> 00:49:51.316
- We have to go.
- What kind of hospital is this?

566
00:49:51.399 --> 00:49:53.985
Is this what we pay health insurance for?

567
00:49:54.068 --> 00:49:56.863
- Where Cathal?
- He's at your sister's with your mum.

568
00:49:56.946 --> 00:49:58.865
- Don't worry.
- I'm not worried.

569
00:49:59.824 --> 00:50:02.619
Right. We've just got you
24-hour police protection.

570
00:50:02.702 --> 00:50:04.787
- OK?
- Grand.

571
00:50:05.872 --> 00:50:10.627
What a way to spend Christmas Eve,
looking at the poxy box.

572
00:50:10.710 --> 00:50:13.546
Mary Poppins. Gone with the Wind.

573
00:50:13.630 --> 00:50:17.425
Next thing you know
it'll be A Wonderful fucking Life.

574
00:50:17.508 --> 00:50:20.261
The doctor says it missed
the artery and the bone.

575
00:50:20.345 --> 00:50:24.766
Point-blank range
with a. 45, and this is all they could do.

576
00:50:24.849 --> 00:50:27.435
- Where's Cathal? How is he?
- He's fine.

577
00:50:27.519 --> 00:50:30.647
Where is he? Oh, yeah. He's with Mum.

578
00:50:30.730 --> 00:50:33.775
- Yeah. He keeps asking for you.
- Yeah?

579
00:50:35.652 --> 00:50:39.322
... shooting happened shortly after...
... investigations for the...

580
00:50:39.405 --> 00:50:42.075
... warning from a crime gang.

581
00:50:44.536 --> 00:50:46.621
You gonna stop this now?

582
00:51:02.554 --> 00:51:04.848
Nan, look! It's Mum!

583
00:51:21.364 --> 00:51:24.534
- Give me the keys.
- I know what I'm doing, Graham.

584
00:51:24.617 --> 00:51:28.955
- They shot me cos I'm on the right track.
- Give me the keys, please.

585
00:51:29.038 --> 00:51:31.708
- Thank you.
- Would you give me the keys?

586
00:51:31.791 --> 00:51:33.626
No.

587
00:51:33.710 --> 00:51:36.212
Look at the state of you.

588
00:51:38.047 --> 00:51:40.717
Do you think I want to do this, do you?

589
00:51:40.800 --> 00:51:43.887
I don't want to do it. I have to do it.

590
00:51:43.970 --> 00:51:47.849
You're a journalist. You write.
You let the Gards look after this.

591
00:51:47.932 --> 00:51:52.228
Oh, Graham, come off it. The Gards
can't do anything. They'll get away with it.

592
00:51:52.312 --> 00:51:54.772
- 14 shootings in 14 months.
- You're one of them.

593
00:51:54.856 --> 00:51:57.775
I know who the guys are.
Would you just give me the keys?

594
00:51:57.859 --> 00:52:00.904
No. Tough shit.

595
00:52:00.987 --> 00:52:03.698
Come on inside. Please.

596
00:52:03.781 --> 00:52:07.368
They're not getting away with it.
I'll catch a cab, then.

597
00:52:07.452 --> 00:52:09.537
Oh, for God's sake.

598
00:52:11.623 --> 00:52:13.708
Ah, Jesus Christ.

599
00:52:14.709 --> 00:52:17.295
Yeah, hi. It's Veronica Guerin. I'd like a...

600
00:52:17.378 --> 00:52:20.423
Thank you. Come on. Get in.

601
00:52:21.424 --> 00:52:24.344
- Who's driving?
- You can't drive with two good legs.

602
00:52:24.427 --> 00:52:27.764
- You think I'll let you drive with one?
- That's low, that is.

603
00:52:27.847 --> 00:52:33.019
- You drive like an old granny.
- Come on, Hopalong, get in.

604
00:52:33.895 --> 00:52:37.398
Where is she going? She only got out
the hospital a couple of days ago.

605
00:52:37.482 --> 00:52:39.567
I know.

606
00:52:49.285 --> 00:52:51.371
You let me do it.

607
00:52:58.127 --> 00:53:02.757
Look! Veronica Guerin.
Come here. Have a look.

608
00:53:02.840 --> 00:53:04.926
Tommy Mullen?

609
00:53:19.440 --> 00:53:21.234
Fatso Mitchell?

610
00:53:22.193 --> 00:53:24.696
- Yeah.
- This is for you.

611
00:53:29.534 --> 00:53:31.619
Get the fuck out of here. Here!

612
00:53:35.164 --> 00:53:39.878
- Your column's upsetting me mother.
- Ah, you poor fella.

613
00:53:39.961 --> 00:53:45.008
You think I'm a drug dealer, don't you?
Well, I'm no drug dealer.

614
00:53:45.091 --> 00:53:49.971
I've seen family and friends dying
week in, week out because of 'em.

615
00:53:50.054 --> 00:53:53.433
All right. Why did you shoot me?

616
00:53:56.060 --> 00:54:00.732
No, I had nothing to do with shooting you.
I wouldn't have missed.

617
00:54:08.531 --> 00:54:11.492
I'm telling you, he isn't here.

618
00:54:11.576 --> 00:54:14.621
And I have to go. I'm busy.

619
00:54:14.704 --> 00:54:17.540
- How old are you?
- None of your business.

620
00:54:17.624 --> 00:54:20.752
Please, just give this to Traynor.

621
00:54:22.086 --> 00:54:25.048
Are you gonna be OK?
I mean, your leg and all?

622
00:54:25.131 --> 00:54:27.467
Yeah, I'm grand.

623
00:54:28.259 --> 00:54:30.637
Are you gonna be all right?

624
00:54:35.517 --> 00:54:40.271
And I thought... I mean, I've always
believed that... Well, I'm a journalist.

625
00:54:40.355 --> 00:54:45.360
Nobody shoots the messenger.
I mean, a journalist doesn't get shot.

626
00:54:45.443 --> 00:54:49.906
If the bullet had hit an artery,
you could have died.

627
00:54:49.989 --> 00:54:52.784
So why do you do it?
Why do you take the risks?

628
00:54:52.867 --> 00:54:59.541
Well, I'll give her this. It takes some balls
to shoot yourself in the leg for publicity.

629
00:54:59.624 --> 00:55:03.211
- She should have shot herself in the balls.
- Bigger target.

630
00:55:03.294 --> 00:55:07.799
- Shall we?
- Never liked this place anyway.

631
00:55:07.882 --> 00:55:13.596
She can always use the insurance money
for a course in journalism.

632
00:55:28.528 --> 00:55:31.322
Here. Check this out.

633
00:55:31.406 --> 00:55:35.159
... bringing to the attention
of the public generally

634
00:55:35.243 --> 00:55:40.498
a culture that exists in our society
that nobody knows anything about.

635
00:55:40.582 --> 00:55:43.501
Your girlfriend's looking
very fucking healthy.

636
00:55:43.585 --> 00:55:45.962
Too bad the moron you hired
shot her in the leg.

637
00:55:46.045 --> 00:55:49.591
Now the whole country's watching her,
thanks to you.

638
00:55:49.674 --> 00:55:53.386
She's a real martyr, thanks to you, Coach.

639
00:55:53.469 --> 00:55:56.514
Saint Veronica of the Sunday Independent.

640
00:55:56.598 --> 00:56:02.103
Relax, will you? She's convinced
it was Gerry Hutch that done it.

641
00:56:02.187 --> 00:56:04.898
You better pray she stays that way.

642
00:56:04.981 --> 00:56:07.192
Come on.

643
00:56:07.275 --> 00:56:09.736
Champagne - now.

644
00:56:09.819 --> 00:56:14.115
These letters that you delivered.
What did you say in them?

645
00:56:14.199 --> 00:56:16.910
There was one simple question
on each of the letters,

646
00:56:16.993 --> 00:56:21.164
and it was
"Were you responsible for my attack?"

647
00:56:32.717 --> 00:56:34.802
Mr Gregory?

648
00:56:34.886 --> 00:56:38.973
What are you doing here? How did you get
past Security? You can't just barge in.

649
00:56:39.057 --> 00:56:42.060
I'm sorry. Do you mind if I sit down?

650
00:56:42.894 --> 00:56:48.066
A young woman wounded, on a crutch.
I'd be at a disadvantage. Take a seat.

651
00:56:48.149 --> 00:56:51.569
I've come to apologise,
if I've got it all wrong.

652
00:56:51.653 --> 00:56:55.198
All of you journalists have got it wrong.

653
00:56:55.990 --> 00:56:58.660
You call these guys the Viper,
the Monk, the General.

654
00:56:58.743 --> 00:57:01.079
You glorify them. They're not movie stars.

655
00:57:01.162 --> 00:57:03.873
With respect, I've no option.

656
00:57:03.957 --> 00:57:07.293
I can't name them.
Your libel laws won't let me.

657
00:57:07.377 --> 00:57:10.046
Journalists are going to jail
for doing their job.

658
00:57:10.129 --> 00:57:13.967
Liz Allen, she's facing imprisonment
for exposing these murderers.

659
00:57:14.050 --> 00:57:16.886
I'm not getting involved
in your personal vendettas.

660
00:57:16.970 --> 00:57:20.682
- I'm not here because I was shot.
- Now we know what you're not here for.

661
00:57:20.765 --> 00:57:26.521
Look, I've been writing quite extensively,
in a balanced way, for the past 18 months.

662
00:57:26.604 --> 00:57:32.068
You must have missed some of my articles.
On June 11th - I just want to clarify this -

663
00:57:32.151 --> 00:57:35.780
I suggested extending
detention periods for drug offenders.

664
00:57:35.864 --> 00:57:40.076
Then on July 16th I wrote about
tax officials - I mean, this is ridiculous -

665
00:57:40.159 --> 00:57:43.121
saying that they are paid
only to record declared income,

666
00:57:43.204 --> 00:57:45.999
not to worry about
whether it comes from drugs.

667
00:57:46.082 --> 00:57:48.793
Then on July 23rd
I wrote about the gardai.

668
00:57:48.877 --> 00:57:53.715
They can seize drug proceeds but can't
hold them. How frustrating is that?

669
00:57:53.798 --> 00:57:58.094
I don't need you to tell me the fight against
drugs has been hampered, crippled,

670
00:57:58.178 --> 00:58:00.847
by the laws that we have at the moment.

671
00:58:00.930 --> 00:58:05.268
- We're on the same side, Mr Gregory.
- We're on the same side?

672
00:58:05.351 --> 00:58:09.355
I don't like your methods,
and I do not like your paper.

673
00:58:09.439 --> 00:58:14.027
Yeah. It's a rag. But it's a popular rag.

674
00:58:14.110 --> 00:58:16.863
Use it. Get your message out. Use me.

675
00:58:16.946 --> 00:58:20.074
You've got to change these laws
that favour the criminals.

676
00:58:20.158 --> 00:58:24.078
